.TH SOFTKMS-DAEMON 8 "February 2025" "softKMS 0.0.1" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
softkms-daemon \- softKMS Key Management Daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B softkms-daemon
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsoftkms-daemon\fR is the core service that provides secure key management
functionality. It runs as a system service and exposes APIs via gRPC and REST
for key operations, identity management, and cryptographic operations.
.PP
The daemon manages encrypted key storage, handles authentication via passphrases
or identity tokens, and provides a complete audit log of all operations.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR
Configuration file path (auto-detected if not specified)
.TP
\fB\-\-user\fR
Force user mode (XDG paths: ~/.config/, ~/.local/share/)
.TP
\fB\-\-system\fR
Force system mode (/etc, /var paths)
.TP
\fB\-\-storage\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR
Storage directory path (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-grpc\-addr\fR \fIADDRESS\fR
gRPC listen address (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-rest\-addr\fR \fIADDRESS\fR
REST API listen address (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-pid\-file\fR \fIFILE\fR
PID file path (default based on run mode)
.TP
\fB\-\-foreground\fR
Run in foreground (do not daemonize)
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level\fR \fILEVEL\fR
Log level: trace, debug, info, warn, error (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-init\fR
Initialize keystore and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-V\fR
Print version information and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Print help information and exit
.SH CONFIGURATION
The daemon auto-detects its run mode and configuration location:
.PP
.B Configuration Discovery Order:
.IP 1. 3
\fB\-\-config <path>\fR (explicit CLI argument)
.IP 2. 3
\fB./softkms.toml\fR (project-local)
.IP 3. 3
\fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/softkms/config.toml\fR (user config)
.IP 4. 3
\fB~/.config/softkms/config.toml\fR (user fallback)
.IP 5. 3
\fB/etc/softkms/config.toml\fR (system-wide)
.IP 6. 3
Built-in defaults
.PP
Run mode is auto-detected based on UID:
.IP \(bu 2
Root (UID 0) \-\> System mode (/etc, /var)
.IP \(bu 2
Regular user \-\> User mode (XDG paths)
.PP
Key configuration sections:
.IP \(bu 2
\fB[storage]\fR \- Data storage backend and encryption settings
.IP \(bu 2
\fB[api]\fR \- gRPC and REST API endpoints
.IP \(bu 2
\fB[logging]\fR \- Log levels and destinations
.IP \(bu 2
\fB[security]\fR \- Session and caching settings
.SH FILES
.SS System Mode (root/system user)
.TP
\fI/etc/softkms/config.toml\fR
System configuration file
.TP
\fI/var/lib/softkms/\fR
System data directory (keys, metadata)
.TP
\fI/var/log/softkms/\fR
System log directory
.TP
\fI/var/log/softkms/audit/\fR
System audit log directory
.TP
\fI/var/run/softkms/\fR
System runtime directory (PID files, sockets)
.SS User Mode (regular user)
.TP
\fI~/.config/softkms/config.toml\fR
User configuration file ($XDG_CONFIG_HOME)
.TP
\fI~/.local/share/softkms/\fR
User data directory ($XDG_DATA_HOME)
.TP
\fI~/.local/state/softkms/\fR
User state directory (logs, audit) ($XDG_STATE_HOME)
.TP
\fI$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/softkms/\fR
User runtime directory (PID files)
.SH SERVICE MANAGEMENT
The daemon is managed by systemd:
.PP
Start the service:
.PP
.nf
.RS
systemctl start softkms
.RE
.fi
.PP
Stop the service:
.PP
.nf
.RS
systemctl stop softkms
.RE
.fi
.PP
Enable at boot:
.PP
.nf
.RS
systemctl enable softkms
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check status:
.PP
.nf
.RS
systemctl status softkms
.RE
.fi
.PP
View logs:
.PP
.nf
.RS
journalctl -u softkms -f
.RE
.fi
.SH SECURITY
When running in system mode, the daemon runs as an unprivileged \fBsoftkms\fR
user with extensive systemd security hardening:
.IP \(bu 2
Read-only filesystem access
.IP \(bu 2
No access to /home directories
.IP \(bu 2
Cannot load kernel modules
.IP \(bu 2
Cannot gain new privileges
.IP \(bu 2
Restricted system calls
.IP \(bu 2
Private /tmp directory
.IP \(bu 2
Network namespace restrictions
.PP
Only \fB/var/lib/softkms\fR, \fB/var/log/softkms\fR, and \fB/var/run/softkms\fR
are writable by the daemon in system mode.
.PP
In user mode, the daemon runs as the invoking user and uses standard XDG
paths for data, state, and runtime files.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Exit status:
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success
.TP
\fB1\fR
General error
.TP
\fB2\fR
Invalid configuration
.TP
\fB3\fR
Keystore not initialized
.TP
\fB4\fR
Permission denied
.TP
\fB5\fR
Address already in use
